# Privacy Policy — HydroMind

**Effective date:** May 1, 2026  

**Last updated:** May 1, 2026  

This Privacy Policy describes how **HydroMind** (“the App”, “we”, “us”) handles information when you use our mobile application published by the developer behind this project. By using the App, you agree to this policy.

---

## Summary

- We **do not operate a login or user account** in the App. **We do not run our own servers** to store your hydration data.
- Your **water logs and preferences are stored locally** on your device.
- **Google AdMob** may process data to show ads. See Google’s disclosures linked below.
- **Reminders** use your device’s **notification** features when you grant permission.

If you disagree with how data is handled, please **uninstall** the App and **avoid using** notification or ad-supported features where applicable.

---

## 1. Who we are

The App is operated by an **independent developer** (publisher of HydroMind).  

**Contact:** replace this line with your public contact email — e.g. `[YOUR_CONTACT_EMAIL]` — for privacy-related requests.

---

## 2. Information the App processes

### 2.1 Data stored on your device (local storage)

The App stores the following **on your device only** using local storage mechanisms (no HydroMind-hosted cloud sync):

- **Settings**, such as: onboarding completion, daily goal, weight used for suggestions, wake/sleep times, reminder intervals, theme preference, measurement units (ml/other), notification sound preference, and similar app configuration.
- **Water intake logs** — amounts and timestamps you log in the App.

You can **clear or remove** this data through in-app controls where available or by **clearing app data / uninstalling** the App.

We **do not** receive this content on our servers, because **we do not provide a backend login or sync service** in the App as shipped.

---

## 3. Notifications

If you **enable reminders** and grant notification permission (Android/iOS):

- The App **schedules local notifications** on your device according to your settings.
- Processing may involve **Apple** (push/notification subsystem on iOS) or **Google** (Android/Firebase-related components as required by the operating system).

We **do not** collect the **content** of your notifications remotely for our own databases as part of normal App behavior described here.

Disable notifications in **system settings** for HydroMind at any time.

---

## 4. Advertising (Google AdMob)

The App may display **advertisements** delivered through **Google Mobile Ads / AdMob** (Google Ireland Limited / Google LLC, depending on region).

Advertising partners may collect and use identifiers and related signals to **measure, personalize, limit frequency, and combat fraud**. That processing is governed by **Google’s policies and your device settings**:

- Google’s Privacy & Terms: <https://policies.google.com/privacy>  
- How Google uses data from apps: <https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites>

You may be able to **opt out of ads personalization** through your device (e.g. Android **Ads settings / Advertising ID**) and through industry tools described by Google where available.

---

## 5. Other technical data

Like most mobile apps, the App and SDKs involved may indirectly process technical information required for **stability, security, billing of ads, fraud prevention**, and compliance with platforms (Apple / Google). We do **not** sell your personal information.

---

## 6. Analytics

The App does **not** integrate a standalone third-party **analytics SDK** solely for HydroMind-hosted analytics in this codebase snapshot. Advertising SDKs **may perform measurement** as described in Section 4.

---

## 7. Children’s privacy

The App is **not directed at children** under 13 (or under the minimum age defined in your region). **Do not** use the App if you are under that age. If you believe a child has provided personal data in a way that concerns you, contact us at the email in Section 1.

---

## 8. International users (including EEA / UK)

If you are in the **European Economic Area**, the **UK**, or **Switzerland**, certain rights may apply under **GDPR** or local law (e.g. access, rectification, erasure, restriction, objection, portability, and the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority).  

Because most data is **on your device**, you can often exercise **erasure** by **deleting app data** or **uninstalling**. For requests related to data processed by **Google** for ads, please also use **Google’s tools and settings** described in their policies.

---

## 9. Data retention

- **Local app data** remains until you **delete** it or **uninstall** the App.
- **Ad partners** retain data according to **their** policies (see Google).

---

## 10. Changes to this policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The **“Last updated”** date at the top will change when we do. Continued use of the App after changes means you accept the updated policy, unless applicable law requires otherwise.

